# Local Lakehouse Platform Delivery & Roadmap

This document outlines the final state of the implemented local Lakehouse platform, structured as a series of clear development sprints. It uses simple English to explain how the platform works and how it was built.

---

## The Final State of the Platform

We have built a **fully functional, local Lakehouse platform** on your machine. 

Instead of using traditional database servers, the platform stores all data (including operational settings, quality rules, and execution history) in **Delta Lake files** directly on your local computer. It uses **PySpark** to process millions of records quickly and safely.

The platform is **generic** (it can handle different types of data by changing settings, not code) and **idempotent** (if a run fails, running it again will not double the data or break anything).

